cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a new architecture for image processing operations, specifically for natural edge detection and thin object segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The architecture is based on a combination of convolutional neural networks and nearest neighbor search, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions underfitting during neural network training, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper validates its approach on challenging benchmarks, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR).
